The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Jan. 28 (PTI): Indira Gandhi International airport today flashed a hijack alert after being unable to communicate with a Kingfisher Airlines flight for seven minutes.          
	The Amritsar-Delhi flight had 50 people on board. Air traffic control sources said the turbo-propped aircraft went out of the radar for seven minutes, sending security personnel at the airport into a tizzy. A spokesperson for the airline denied the incident and said it was a false rumour that our flight from Amritsar to New Delhi lost contact with the radar.                  
	 Madurai (PTI): Madras High Court has ruled that a vehicle owner cannot claim compensation from the regional transport officer or police for not taking proper care of his seized vehicle unless he proves malicious intent on the part of the officials.                  
	 Dehra Dun (PTI): Shooting photographs of women taking a bath at the Maha Kumbh Mela in Haridwar will not be allowed and criminal cases will be filed against those violating the directive, the Uttarakhand chief minister has said. The administration has received complaints that journalists have been taking pictures of bathing women.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Delhi state consumer commission has denied the insurance claim of a truck owner whose vehicle met with an accident in Punjab where it was plying without permit.                                                                                                                                              
